{"affected_servers":["server-c1"],"cluster":"C","description":"server-c1 is currently serving traffic from the configuration loaded at startup, but /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf has been corrupted afterward by the entrypoint script. As a result, nginx configuration validation and reloads fail, preventing safe configuration changes or service reloads and creating operational risk on the next restart/redeploy.","issue":"Nginx continues serving but the active configuration file is deliberately corrupted after startup, making config validation/reload fail. Root cause: server-c1 entrypoint.sh appends an unterminated server block containing an invalid directive to /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf after nginx has started.","remediation":"Run this on server-c1 as root. It backs up the files, removes entrypoint lines/heredocs that append to /etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf, restores a valid default server config, validates it, and reloads Nginx. If server-c1 is container/image-built, also apply this entrypoint change in the image/source repo and redeploy so it persists.

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

CONF=/etc/nginx/conf.d/default.conf
ENTRYPOINT=${ENTRYPOINT:-}
if [[ -z "$ENTRYPOINT" ]]; then
  for p in /entrypoint.sh /usr/local/bin/entrypoint.sh /docker-entrypoint.sh /usr/local/bin/docker-entrypoint.sh; do
    [[ -f "$p" ]] && ENTRYPOINT="$p" && break
  done
fi
[[ -f "$ENTRYPOINT" ]] || { echo "Set ENTRYPOINT=/path/to/entrypoint.sh and rerun" >&2; exit 1; }

ts=$(date +%Y%m%d%H%M%S)
cp -a "$ENTRYPOINT" "$ENTRYPOINT.bak.$ts"
cp -a "$CONF" "$CONF.bak.$ts"

tmp=$(mktemp)
skip=0
delim=
while IFS= read -r line || [[ -n "$line" ]]; do
  if [[ "$skip" -eq 1 ]]; then
    trimmed=$(printf '%s\n' "$line" | sed 's/^[[:space:]]*//;s/[[:space:]]*$//')
    [[ "$trimmed" == "$delim" ]] && skip=0
    continue
  fi

  if [[ "$line" == *"$CONF"* && ( "$line" == *">>"* || "$line" =~ tee[[:space:]]+-a ) ]]; then
    if [[ "$line" == *"<<"* ]]; then
      delim=${line#*<<}
      delim=${delim#-}
      delim=$(printf '%s\n' "$delim" | awk '{print $1}' | tr -d "'\"")
      skip=1
    fi
    continue
  fi

  printf '%s\n' "$line" >> "$tmp"
done < "$ENTRYPOINT"
cat "$tmp" > "$ENTRYPOINT"
rm -f "$tmp"
chmod +x "$ENTRYPOINT"

cat > "$CONF" <<'NGINX'
server {
    listen 80 default_server;
    listen [::]:80 default_server;
    server_name _;
    root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    index index.html index.htm;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ =404;
    }
}
NGINX

nginx -t
nginx -s reload 2>/dev/null || systemctl reload nginx
```","severity":4,"ticket_id":"b0fa6cb9-a3a2-4697-b2d7-576aadcd21d8"}

